## Limitations

The findings in this report are based on available online resources and may not encompass all perspectives on the issue. The debate over the death penalty is complex and multifaceted, with cultural, legal, and ethical dimensions that vary across different regions and legal systems. Additionally, the data on the deterrent effect of the death penalty is mixed and often influenced by methodological differences in studies. Further research, including empirical studies and expert interviews, would provide a more comprehensive understanding of the issue.